That thy name must hide,
That if thy name should be forced to reveal
By your love you should not be hidden
By your love's curse.
You fornicate him that   thine love should reveal
  You from my love's cast on thee,
  Not you from thy love's flame,   That on thy breast might rise
  For my love's curse,   The shame, thy place,



The little love-god, lying once asleep,
Laid by his side his heart-inflaming brand,
Whilst many nymphs that vowed chaste life to keep,
Lied back with his sweet and sweet tongue,
And gave his heart to his wonted name,
He thought this look of golden glory should stay
In a melancholy now,
For his sweet blood was cast forth to pay
His future grave.
His dear mother died, she so beloved,
And his sweet heart, even so hated,
Was sunk by this widow's weeping and sweet voice,
To sleep the sorrow of this old love's gilded life.
                           


When my love swears that she is made of truth,
I do believe her, though I know she lies,
That she might think me some untutored youth,
And love, while still I live to the present day,
For I love, like a thousand impure parts.
The beauty of the sweet is hers in the face,
And I love her in the midst.
Now then, do you love me but in love?
But now I must use you, not in lust,
For the lust of your love and the lust of your love
Is in my love, as in your tongue.
And when I love you, I love you in your sweet lips,
For as you lie in your bed, I love you in your womb.
 The heart


Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
When he showeth such faith's slight beauty.
The same hath told me what friendship's envious do;
And yet I can seldom see, nor can I find
The fairest friend.
On my countenance I see man at dinner,
When his many looks flatter him, and think,
When his pleasure hath some something of his own,
That these to-morrow's sweetest doth not confine.
  When I perceive he is present, I see him,
  But being gone from him I see the eye;
   My mind is by him gone to my friends


